HEADWORD: Pollucite
<hw>Pol"lu*cite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Pollux</er>, and 4th <er>Castor</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A colorless transparent mineral, resembling quartz, occurring with
castor or castorite on the island of Elba. It is a silicate of alumina
and c⟦ae⟧sia. Called also <altname>pollux</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

